values:
this is the end of livejournal for me.

goodbye.

well, my cat is a boy. miko, is a boy.

i guess it's too late to change his name.. ..

anyway, this summer is still just dragging on.  i really have nothing noteworthy to say.

no one reads this anyway.

eh.

i miss kaleena. and i want to go home or to the beach. i want to feel like i'm really having a summer and fucking enjoy it.

i want something to happen. i need to make something happen.

summer is still boring, but now miko is here in huntington to stay. she's getting bigger and attacks me and brewer all the time. she's certainly cute, but she leaves scratches like these all over our bodies. nice. and yes, that is the side of my face. i've got to find something to do with my time. i think i'll go buy a new book.

Fags today are all about body building and pickup trucks, and straight guys are all about feelings and open-toe sandals." haha. ;]

okay, huntington is extremely boring during the summer.

i should have just gotten a job.

this sucks.

someone call me. all i do now is read and play video games.

last night, i dreamt that i was attacked by richard greico at my home in logan and then i stabbed him in the heart and chopped him up. i fled to jenna's house where i received news from my mom that he was STILL alive and searching for me.

talk about a weird nightmare.

richard greico.. pfft.

and, his name in my dream was freddie vector.

hilarious.

i'm in logan now, and i have a new kitten. :) it's only about 3 weeks old, and i don't know what the sex is yet. it's really hard to tell.. but i named it miko. it's the cutest kitten in the world.

did you know they replaced lemon jolly ranchers ( the best flavor, might i add) with blue raspberry? i'm pretty upset about that!

well, it's 4:00 am and yoshimi just left my apartment to fly back to japan.

this is terrible.

second update.

you know, i'm just not feeling well at all right now.

i'm having some issues and i realize i have absolutely no one to talk to.

i've been thinking about everythng that has happened over this semester.. and it's just making me sad.
everything's going to change.
i don't know if i want that..

right now, i feel like this summer is absolutely going to suck.






i'm sorry.

"His name is a word on top of a page and it signifies a poem started, stated, started but unfinished since the typewriter will not type anymore. I kiss my hand and smell it and smell him, oh I pretend it is his scent. His. His. I don't dare go to his house or pass his room. I will walk by him and not even look. I will pass him in the dinning hall with a nonchalance that shocks even me."

waiting until today to come home was a good idea.
i really can't handle a whole weekend of doing nothing, even though it's only a couple days.
kristen spent the night with me last night and we basically ate all night long.
well, i did.
i also made an elephant out of clay and he looks awesome. i named him ebner.

i came to several realizations while coming home today.
i feel a lot better.
but kind of surprised at the same time.

:)

and i finally got a new phone! i still have the same number though.

hmm. nice.

one of my hermit crabs is walking around with no shell on. it's pretty creepy and i don't know what to do.
i'm getting wrinkles on my forehead from squinting at this computer screen every single day of my life.

i got up at 8:30 a.m. only to realize after i had gotten ready that i wanted to skip the class i have at 11:00.

so, i've been sitting here practically doing nothing all day, keeping myself awake for really no reason.
only to go to class at 6:30.
for the first time.

it's the third week of school, and i haven't been to this class one time.

ah well.

my stomach feels all icky.
and i don't see this day getting any more exciting.

these nights of drinking just get a little more interesting every time.
but i don't think i'm going to be drinking again for a while. i do stupid things when i'm drunk and i hate worrying about shit the next day.



and i swear, there was an eleven year old here last night.
weird.




our cat likes wonton soup.

mental note: never stay home for more than one day at a time. 

god.
